Analyzed Genes and Target

We define the genes for classification, the expected target gene and the classification criteria.

U2.genes <- c("FUBP1","SF1","U2AF1","U2AF2","SNRPB","SNRPD1","SNRPD2",
              "SNRPD3","SNRPE","SNRPF","SNRPG","PUF60","SMNDC1",
              "DNAJC8","RBM17","CHERP","U2SURP","DHX15","DDX46","CELF6",
              "PCBP1")

target.genes <- U2.genes

# possible methods: "del.vs.non.del", "del.vs.non.mut","mut.vs.non.mut"
classification.method <- "del.vs.non.mut"

In this analysis, the U2 genes are used for classification. The expected target gene is FUBP1, SF1, U2AF1, U2AF2, SNRPB, SNRPD1, SNRPD2, SNRPD3, SNRPE, SNRPF, SNRPG, PUF60, SMNDC1, DNAJC8, RBM17, CHERP, U2SURP, DHX15, DDX46, CELF6, PCBP1.

Data Exploration

Mutations in U2 Genes

mutation.stats.DRIVE <- as.data.frame(cbind(U2.genes,non.del.mut=NA,del.mut=NA))
mutation.stats.Achilles <- mutation.stats.DRIVE

for (gene in U2.genes) {
  # keep only cell lines with mutations in current gene
  CCLE.mut.gene <- CCLE.mut[CCLE.mut$Hugo_Symbol==gene,]
  
  # remove mutation entries with more harmless mutation
  # in genes with multiple mutations
  CCLE.mut.gene <- CCLE.mut.gene[order(CCLE.mut.gene$isDeleterious,
                                             decreasing=T),]
  CCLE.mut.gene <- CCLE.mut.gene[!duplicated(CCLE.mut.gene$DepMap_ID),]
  
  # remove silent mutations
  CCLE.mut.gene <- 
    CCLE.mut.gene[CCLE.mut.gene$Variant_Classification!="Silent",]
  
  # characters to boolean
  CCLE.mut.gene$isDeleterious <- ifelse(
    CCLE.mut.gene$isDeleterious=="True", TRUE, FALSE)
  
  # add columns for deleterious mutated and mutated, but non-deleterious
  CCLE.mut.gene$isMutated <- ifelse(
    CCLE.mut.gene$isDeleterious,"deleterious mutated","non-deleterious mutated")

  # replace DepMap_IDs by CCLE names
  CCLE.mut.gene <- merge(CCLE.mut.gene,cancer.names,by="DepMap_ID")
  CCLE.mut.gene$DepMap_ID <- NULL
  CCLE.mut.gene <- 
    CCLE.mut.gene[,c("CCLE_ID","Variant_Classification","isDeleterious")]
  
  # keep only cell lines for which dependency scores are available
  CCLE.mut.gene.DRIVE <- merge(CCLE.mut.gene,dep.scores.DRIVE['CCLE_ID'],
                                by="CCLE_ID")
  CCLE.mut.gene.Achilles <- merge(CCLE.mut.gene,
                                   dep.scores.Achilles['CCLE_ID'],by="CCLE_ID")
  
  # count deleterious mutated and non-deleterious mutated cell lines
  counts.del.mut.DRIVE <- 
    nrow(CCLE.mut.gene.DRIVE[CCLE.mut.gene.DRIVE$isDeleterious==T,])
  counts.non.del.mut.DRIVE <- 
    nrow(CCLE.mut.gene.DRIVE[CCLE.mut.gene.DRIVE$isDeleterious==F,])
  
  counts.del.mut.Achilles <- 
    nrow(CCLE.mut.gene.Achilles[CCLE.mut.gene.Achilles$isDeleterious==T,])
  counts.non.del.mut.Achilles <- 
    nrow(CCLE.mut.gene.Achilles[CCLE.mut.gene.Achilles$isDeleterious==F,])
  
  mutation.stats.DRIVE[mutation.stats.DRIVE$U2.genes==gene,]$del.mut <- 
    counts.del.mut.DRIVE
  mutation.stats.DRIVE[mutation.stats.DRIVE$U2.genes==gene,]$non.del.mut <- 
    counts.non.del.mut.DRIVE
  
  mutation.stats.Achilles[mutation.stats.Achilles$U2.genes==gene,]$del.mut <- 
    counts.del.mut.Achilles
  mutation.stats.Achilles[
    mutation.stats.Achilles$U2.genes==gene,]$non.del.mut <- 
    counts.non.del.mut.Achilles
  
  # why is this not numeric?
  mutation.stats.DRIVE$non.del.mut <- 
    as.integer(mutation.stats.DRIVE$non.del.mut)
  mutation.stats.DRIVE$del.mut <- as.integer(mutation.stats.DRIVE$del.mut)
  mutation.stats.Achilles$non.del.mut <- 
    as.integer(mutation.stats.Achilles$non.del.mut)
  mutation.stats.Achilles$del.mut <- as.integer(mutation.stats.Achilles$del.mut)
}

Classification Tables for U2 genes

Now we create a classification table in which each cell line is classified as deleterious if at least one U2 gene has a deleterious mutation.

create.classification.table <- switch(classification.method,
                "del.vs.non.del" = create.classification.table.del.vs.non.del,
                "del.vs.non.mut" = create.classification.table.del.vs.non.mut,
                "mut.vs.non.mut" = create.classification.table.mut.vs.non.mut)

# create data structure
class.table.U2 <- create.classification.table(CCLE.mut, cancer.names,
                                              U2.genes[1], dep.scores.DRIVE,
                                              dep.scores.Achilles)
class.table.U2.DRIVE <- class.table.U2$DRIVE
class.table.U2.Achilles <- class.table.U2$Achilles

for (gene in U2.genes) {
  class.table <- create.classification.table(CCLE.mut, cancer.names,
                                             gene, dep.scores.DRIVE,
                                             dep.scores.Achilles)
  class.table.DRIVE <- class.table$DRIVE
  class.table.Achilles <- class.table$Achilles
  
  # merge with existing classifications
  class.table.DRIVE <- merge(class.table.U2.DRIVE,class.table.DRIVE,
                             by="CCLE_ID",all = TRUE)
  class.table.DRIVE[is.na(class.table.DRIVE)] <- FALSE
  class.table.DRIVE$isDeleterious <- ifelse(class.table.DRIVE$isDeleterious.x |
                                              class.table.DRIVE$isDeleterious.y,
                                            TRUE, FALSE)
  class.table.DRIVE$isDeleterious.x <- NULL
  class.table.DRIVE$isDeleterious.y <- NULL
  
  class.table.U2.DRIVE <- class.table.DRIVE
  
  # do the same with Achilles
  class.table.Achilles <- merge(class.table.U2.Achilles,class.table.Achilles,
                             by="CCLE_ID",all = TRUE)
  class.table.Achilles[is.na(class.table.Achilles)] <- FALSE
  class.table.Achilles$isDeleterious <- ifelse(
    class.table.Achilles$isDeleterious.x | class.table.Achilles$isDeleterious.y,
    TRUE, FALSE)
  class.table.Achilles$isDeleterious.x <- NULL
  class.table.Achilles$isDeleterious.y <- NULL
  
  class.table.U2.Achilles <- class.table.Achilles
}

Mean Differences

test.results <- calc.mean.diffs.and.p.values(dep.scores.DRIVE, 
                                           dep.scores.Achilles,
